TML document.\n\n```\nparam root\n\nAn ElementTree \nfor the root element of a document.\nIf the given element is not the root,\nselector matching will behave is if it were.\nIn other words, selectors will be not be scoped\nto the subtree rooted at that element.\n\nreturns\n\nA new \n```\n\n[scoped]: https://drafts.csswg.org/selectors-4/#scoping\n"]}, {"name": "cssselect2.tree.ElementWrapper.from_html_root", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "root", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "content_language", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Same as {meth}`from_xml_root` with case-insensitive attribute names.\n\nUseful for documents parsed with an HTML parser like html5lib, which\nshould be the case of documents with the `text/html` MIME type.\n"]}, {"name": "cssselect2.tree.ElementWrapper._from_root", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "root", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "content_language", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "in_html_document", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cssselect2.tree.ElementWrapper.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "etree_element", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "parent", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "index", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "previous", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "in_html_document", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "content_language", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cssselect2.tree.ElementWrapper.__eq__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "other", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cssselect2.tree.ElementWrapper.__ne__", "asynchronous":