sting {class}`ElementWrapper` objects for this\nelement\u2019s previous siblings, in reversed tree order.\n\nThe element itself is not included, this is an empty sequence for a\nfirst child or the root element.\n\nThis method is deprecated and will be removed in version 0.7.0. Use\n{attr}`previous_siblings` instead.\n"]}, {"name": "cssselect2.tree.ElementWrapper.iter_siblings", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Iterate over siblings.\n\nReturn an iterator of newly-created {class}`ElementWrapper` objects for\nthis element\u2019s siblings, in tree order.\n"]}, {"name": "cssselect2.tree.ElementWrapper.iter_next_siblings", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Iterate over next siblings.\n\nReturn an iterator of newly-created {class}`ElementWrapper` objects for\nthis element\u2019s next siblings, in tree order.\n"]}, {"name": "cssselect2.tree.ElementWrapper.iter_children", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Iterate over children.\n\nReturn an iterator of newly-created {class}`ElementWrapper` objects for\nthis element\u2019s child elements, in tree order.\n"]}, {"name": "cssselect2.tree.ElementWrapper.iter_subtree", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Iterate over subtree.\n\nReturn an iterator of newly-created {class}`ElementWrapper` objects for\nthe entire subtree rooted at this element, in tree order.\n\nUnlike in other methods, the element itself *is* included.\n\nThis loops over an entire document:\n\n```python\nfor element in ElementWrapper.from_root(root_etree).iter_subtree():\n    ...\n```\n"]}, {"name": "cssselect2.tree.ElementWrapper._compile", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "selectors", "type": null, "default": null}]